programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time
programme.desc: Namibia is an arid, rough land. However, it has been inhabited for thousands of years, by people as well as animals, and shows no sign of losing popularity with either.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Vancouver Island: Rivers of Life
programme.desc: Vancouver island is the largest island off the west coast of North America. Glaciers fuel the flow of some of Canada's tallest waterfalls, and an endless network of rivers and creeks provides the ideal habitat for the pacific salmon.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise
programme.desc: The Caribbean is a tropical paradise. From just a few meters wide, to hundreds of kilometers across, each of the over 7,000 islands are different, and each has its own unique wildlife.
programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island
programme.desc: Lying like a teardrop in the Indian Ocean, Sri Lanka is an island that defies convention. Poised just six degrees above the equator, it's less than 75,000 km sq in size. But it has enough wildlife to rival a continent.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Falkland Islands: Penguin Paradise
programme.desc: The Falkland's bleak, battered, and windswept archipelago lies 460 km from the South American mainland. Rugged mountains and expansive pristine coastline are a unique home for wildlife  especially for one of the world's most iconic flightless birds.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds
programme.desc: The longest chain of mountains in the world, the Andes run the length of western South America and dictate the climate for the whole continent. They include some of the highest peaks outside the Himalayas.
programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Holiday Wishes
programme.desc: Britney, a rich, spoiled child, and Rachel, an orphan, switch bodies after a visit to the mall with Santa Claus. Each girl wakes up as the other - Britney is in the orphanage, and Rachel is at Britney's family's mansion.

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland

programme.desc: For centuries, farmers have been discovering strange, complex geometric patterns comprised of rings, circles and other intricate shapes in their fields.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard meets the owners of an abnormal humanoid skull allegedly discovered in Mexico in the 1930s and a researcher who has had the skull subjected to numerous tests including carbon-14 dating, and DNA in order to determine it’s origin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Mystery of Oak Island
programme.desc: Richard investigates Canada's best-known mysteries, the Oak Island treasure. Also known as the money pit, the site has become one of the world's deepest and most costly archaeological digs.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Energy Healing
programme.desc: Several energy healers claim they are able to produce spontaneous miraculous healing through a laying on of hands. Claims of similar such healing by a man in a remote village in Brazil, known as John of God are also examined.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray
programme.desc: In this re-examination of the assassination of civil rights leader Martin Luther King, Richard meets several researchers who provide evidence that the convicted gunman, James Earl Ray was not the real triggerman.
programme.sub-title: The Execution of MLK and The Framing of James Earl Ray

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Birthers - Obama's Birth Certificate
programme.desc: Richard interviews several prominent 'Birthers' who present evidence that proves Barack Obama is not eligible to be President because he does not meet the qualifications of a natural born citizen.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: RFID Chips
programme.desc: Could implantable RFID chips or Radio-frequency identification tags currently in widespread use in retail industry be used to surreptitiously track and control people?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Assassination of John Lennon
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show travels to New York, LA and Toronto in order to investigate the murder of John Lennon. Several researchers posit that Lennon's supposed killer Mark David Chapman was either a patsy or a mind-controlled assassin.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?
programme.desc: Is it conceivable that the Doors legendary front man did not die in a bathtub in Paris of an apparent drug overdose?
programme.sub-title: Did Jim Morrison Fake His Death?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Water Engine
programme.desc: Did the late Stanley Meyer figure out a way to run an internal combustion engine on pure water? And was he murdered because of the threat his invention posed to Big Oil?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Murder of Marilyn Monroe
programme.desc: Did this pop icon and blond bombshell succumb to a drug overdose in 1962 as we've been led to believe or was she killed for 'knowing too much?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims that the medical profession, drug companies, the food industry and government agencies are suppressing a cure for cancer.
programme.sub-title: Is The Cure for Cancer Being Suppressed?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Bilderbergs
programme.desc: A glimpse backstage at the highly secretive annual gathering of the world's richest and most powerful movers and shakers.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Shroud of Turin
programme.desc: Is this famous piece of linen cloth the actual burial cloth of Jesus Christ or a clever Medieval hoax?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: The Fake Arab Spring?
programme.desc: Who was really behind a series of revolts, protests, and uprisings that swept the Middle East starting in late 2010?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Ouija Boards?
programme.desc: Harmless board game or portal to the spirit world? Richard delves into the history and folklore of 'talking boards' with a collector of Ouija boards and a world renowned paranormal investigator.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Global Warming, A Hoax?
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several journalists and researchers who argue the theory that human use of carbon-based fossil fuels will lead to catastrophic global warming.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: JFK
programme.desc: Richard meets with some prominent JFK assassination researchers to discuss the November 1963 murder of President John F. Kennedy.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Pterodactyls
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several explorers and cryptozoologists who believe pterodactyls, flying dinosaurs thought to have become extinct some 60 million years ago, are alive and thriving in remote places such as Papua New Guinea.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: GMO - Genetically Modified Food
programme.desc: Richard investigates claims crop plants created for human or animal consumption using the latest molecular biology techniques are unsafe.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Fluoride
programme.desc: The Conspiracy Show investigates the safety and efficacy of putting fluoride in our water supply. Dentists say that putting fluoride in the water supply prevents tooth decay, but some researchers claim it's a toxic substance that causes cancer.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Area 51
programme.desc: What's going on inside Area 51, America's most carefully guarded secret? The mysterious military base located 30 minutes north west of Las Vegas has been rumored to be involved in back engineering advanced alien technology recovered from UFO crash sites.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Remote Viewing
programme.desc: We meet several individuals who claim they have the ability to transcend time and space and identify people, objects, and locations hidden from their view.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett: Freemasons
programme.desc: Are the Freemasons a harmless fraternity whose members busy themselves by raising money for children's hospitals or a satanic cult whose tentacles and enslave mankind?

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett
programme.desc: Richard speaks with several independent researchers about the efforts of international bankers to control the course of history and enslave humanity through their monopoly of the creation of money and the manipulation of the money supply.

programme.title: The Conspiracy Show With Richard Syrett

programme.sub-title: The Hunt for the Book of Spells

programme.sub-title: The Mystery of Thomas Beale's Treasure

programme.title: Angry Planet: Volcanic Wedding

programme.title: Angry Planet: Venezuela Lightning
programme.desc: Gas from Catatumbo swamps mixed with cold air from the Andes create a perpetual lightning storm on South America's largest lake. From here George canoes 84 km to world's highest waterfall, swims with piranhas and holds a huge Anaconda.

programme.title: Angry Planet: Elephant Cave

programme.title: Angry Planet: Midwest Stormfest

programme.title: Angry Planet: Indonesia

programme.title: Angry Planet: Tornadoes

programme.title: Naked Science: Anatomy Of Tornado
programme.desc: Tornados are one of the most destructive forces of the planets with winds at 300 miles an hour. They can destroy buildings and hurl cars hundreds of feet through the air.

programme.title: Naked Science: Mars
programme.desc: Mars our closest neighbor now a lifeless planet – but it may once have had water and therefore life. Naked Science investigates the red planet to learn how it was formed, how it became barren, and ask whether it ever will be possible to colonize it?

programme.title: Naked Science: Great Lakes
programme.desc: The Great Lakes are sometimes referred to as inland seas; they are the largest freshwater system in the world. Naked Science examines the early history of these amazing bodies

programme.title: Naked Science: How To Destroy A Planet
programme.desc: The Earth is built to last. It is a 4,550,000,000-year-old, 5,973,600,000,000,000,000,000-tonne ball of rock and iron. It has taken more devastating asteroid hits in its lifetime than you've had hot dinners, and it still orbits happily around the sun.

programme.title: Naked Science: Death Of The Earth
programme.desc: The earth is 4.5 billion years old and it is slowly dying. Tectonic activity is slowly cooling the planet – the continents will eventually move together to form a new supercontinent called Pangea Ultima.

programme.title: Naked Science: What's Wrong With Pluto
programme.desc: Naked Science investigates the violent cosmological forces that create planets and discover what it is that makes a planet a planet.

programme.title: Naked Science: Jupiter
programme.desc: By far the largest planet, 1300 times the size of Earth, it’s a world so enormous it could swallow every planet and moon in the solar system and still have room to spare.

programme.title: Naked Science: Diamonds
programme.desc: Naked Science follows the story of a diamond from the creation of carbon inside the heart of a dying sun, through to the cutting of a diamond mine in South Africa.

programme.title: Naked Science: Inside The Mind Of Stephen Hawking

programme.desc: Homemade gules to test stickiness; puzzle with a scientific optical illusion; supersonic car.

programme.desc: The science of genetic modification in Hawaii; shattering a glass; curing a dust allergy through eating worms.

programme.title: Bang Goes The Theory

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanoes
programme.desc: There are few sights on earth as compelling as a volcanic eruption. Volcanoes have the potential to cause death and widespread destruction in a heartbeat, but they also give rise to new life and ecosystems.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: War Story: D-Day plus 1
programme.desc: The Canadian stand against the 12th SS Panzer Division Hitlerjugend immediately after D-Day allowed the Allies to switch to the offensive and truly begin the liberation of Europe.

programme.title: War Story: Surviving Dieppe
programme.desc: The Dieppe assault of 19 August 1942 is the worst day in Canadian military history: in just 8 hours, 907 Canadians were killed. For 2,000 of their comrades, nearly three years of incarceration in German prison camps followed.

programme.title: War Story: Whistle for a Tiffy
programme.desc: From D-Day, Tactical Air Force fighter-bombers played a pivotal role in Allied battlefield success; Canadian soldiers knew they could always “whistle for a Tiffy”.

programme.title: War Story: Behind Enemy Lines
programme.desc: Royal Canadian Air Force bombing operations play a crucial role in disrupting German infrastructure ahead of the Normandy invasion of June 1944. In the process, dozens of Canadian airmen are forced to bail out over occupied Belgium and France.

programme.title: War Story: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad
programme.desc: In the summer of 1942, the Germans advance to seize the rich oilfields of the Caucasus. In their path, the city of Stalingrad, its Soviet defenders personally ordered by Stalin to “take not one step back".
programme.sub-title: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad

programme.title: War Story: Buchenwald Airmen
programme.desc: For two months in 1944, 168 Allied airmen were shot down over occupied France, betrayed to the Gestapo by the same collaborator, transported to the Nazi concentration and slave labour camp Buchenwald.

programme.title: War Story: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt
programme.desc: On 16 April 1945, a mere three weeks before German surrender, the submarine fired a single torpedo that sank the last Canadian naval vessel lost to enemy action.
programme.sub-title: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt

programme.title: War Story: Prisoners of the Sun
programme.desc: On 16 November 1941, two Canadian battalions arrived in the British colony of Hong Kong. Their aim: Bolster the Empire’s defenses in the event of aggression by the restless forces of Japan, stationed only kilometres away in occupied China.

programme.title: War Story: Vengeance
programme.desc: In 1941, nearly 30,000 Jews escaped the ghettos and work camps and they joined the growing underground resistance army, actively fighting the Nazis.

programme.title: War Story: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany
programme.desc: In mid-September 1944, the remnants of the battered 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion participated in the largest parachute drop in history, fought a successful battle.
programme.sub-title: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany

programme.title: War Story: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy
programme.desc: In Normandy, the 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion proved itself to be in the vanguard of the best-trained and toughest units in the Allied forces.
programme.sub-title: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy

programme.title: War Story: The Road to Rome
programme.desc: The Road to Rome examines the incredible experiences of Canadian veterans, the victories and horrors of armoured combat, and the pivotal value, far too often neglected, of the overall Italian Campaign.

programme.title: War Story: Ortona: The War Inside
programme.desc: The War Inside is a personal retelling of one of the fiercest battles of the Italian Campaign from the searing points of view of Canadian infantrymen, a tanker, a stretcher bearer, and a German paratrooper.

programme.title: War Story: Sicily: The First Campaign
programme.desc: The Sicily Campaign began with the largest seaborne invasion in history on 9-10 July 1943. The Allied forces of Britain, Canada, and the United States sought to knock Italy out of the war and attack Germany from the south.

programme.title: War Story: Bomb Girls Remember
programme.desc: During the Second World War, 250,000 Canadian women helped to build the arsenal of democracy. These young women met the challenges of factory work and helped to win the Second World War, and by doing so, paved the way for future generations.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Getting Home
programme.desc: In this film, Bomber Command personnel and a Luftwaffe pilot take the viewer through the frightening reality of fighting in the skies as they try to get a damaged bomber home.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Hitting Back
programme.desc: After surviving the German bombing campaign of British cities, RAF Bomber Command struck back against Germany. The devastating consequences of raids, for both for the young men in the skies and the people on the ground, are portrayed in this film.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan continues its suicidal resistance, and invading it looks costly. After 2 atomic bombs, the Emperor intervenes and stops the War. Stalin grabs territory in East Asia. The War is over, and the Atomic Era and the Cold War start.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: In 1945, Germany is crumbly on both fronts. The Western Allies cross the Rhine and take most of Germany, while the Red Army quickly advances into Berlin. After Hitler's suicide, Germany surrenders and is divided among the allied powers.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Marines succeed in the "island hopping" strategy against suicidal resistance. The US Navy establishes supremacy, cutting off Japan.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Western Allies secure supply routes that will allow them to enter Germany, and the Ardennes counter-offensive fails. The Red Army advances rapidly. The SS implements the Holocaust.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: After a careful campaign of disinformation that throws the German defenders off-guard, the Western Allies finally land on Normandy.France is liberated.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Their attack on the Soviet Union having failed, the German Army suffers a series of counter-offensives on the Eastern Front. Wehrmacht's losses are huge as the Soviets advance West.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Allies turn the tide in the Atlantic, where initially German U-Boats harass freely convoys to supply Britain. The route to bring American soldiers who will land on D-Day is clear.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Italy's failed attacks in the Mediterranean region draw in the Germans.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan attacks the USA on 7 Dec 1941. For the next 6 months, they continue to have successful attacks.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The German invasion of Russia from Operation Barbarossa on 22 June 1941 to Kursk on 5 July 1943.

programme.title: Waiting For Fidel
programme.desc: Three Canadians, including ex-premier Joseph Smallwood and NFB director Michael Rubbo, travel to Cuba, aiming to cast Fidel Castro. Their journey offers insights into Cuba's changes and their own views.

programme.title: Gurdeep Singh Bains
programme.desc: Gurdeep is a thirteen-year-old Canadian Sikh whose family runs a dairy farm near Chilliwack, British Columbia. They have retained their language and religion. Sometimes he feels a little different from the other children because he wears a turban.

programme.title: Sunrise Over Tiananmen Square
programme.desc: Shui-Bo Wang's animated documentary intertwines personal journey with history, exploring China's '60s-'80s upheavals. From symbol of hope to tragedy, it depicts Wang's roles from Red Guard to teacher, exploring idealism and intolerance.

programme.title: Toward Intimacy
programme.desc: Toward Intimacy" celebrates the rights of women with disabilities to pursue intimate relationships. This one-hour film features personal stories from four Canadian women, addressing sexuality, self-esteem, stereotypes, and parenting.

programme.title: The Glass Ceiling
programme.desc: Whether in the public service or on the shop floor, discrimination against women is taking on increasingly subtle forms, which makes it even more difficult to eliminate.

programme.title: Challenger An Industrial Romance
programme.desc: Follows the development of Canadair's super-executive jet. The film captures the spirit of the Canadian air transport industry and its attempt to compete with the American leaders in the industry.

programme.title: Spirit Of The Kata
programme.desc: Five women, all of them black belts in karate, are examples of how this ancient martial art can transform lives. They demonstrate how it can generate a whole range of physical, psychological and spiritual benefits.

programme.title: First Stories - Two Spirited
programme.desc: This short documentary presents the empowering story of Rodney "Geeyo" Poucette's struggle against prejudice in the Indigenous community as a two spirited person (gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender).

programme.title: If You Love This Planet
programme.desc: This film records a lecture given to students by outspoken nuclear critic, Dr. Helen Caldicott, president of Physicians for Social Responsibility in the United States. Her message is clear: disarmament cannot be postponed.

programme.title: Kathleen Shannon On Film Feminism Other Dreams
programme.desc: With intelligence and humour, documentary filmmaker, Kathleen Shannon speaks her formative years at the National Film Board, and the gradual awakening of an unshakeable determination to give women filmmakers a chance to tell their stories of the world

programme.title: Chaque Enfant
programme.desc: This is the story of a baby who appears mysteriously on the doorstep of a busy executive, and who is subsequently bounced from household to household down the block. Nobody in the community is interested in caring for the baby without a name.

programme.title: Horse Drawn Magic
programme.desc: The Caravan Stage Company is the only horse-drawn open-air theatre in the world. Every summer it tours British Columbia and Alberta, bringing live entertainment to communities where television is often the main diversion.

programme.title: The Impossible Takes A Little Longer
programme.desc: Documents the work and personal lives of five physically disabled women. It shows how they are coping with the problems they share with all women, the problems they share with other disabled women and those unique to their particular circumstances.

programme.title: Holy Angels
programme.desc: Jay Cardinal Villeneuve’s short documentary Holy Angels powerfully recaptures Canada’s colonialist history through impressionistic images and the fragmented language of a child.

programme.title: Julie Obrien
programme.desc: This film is loosely structured around Julie O'Brien, eleven’s school assignment to write an essay about the old times in Newfoundland, how they have changed, how they are still remembered.

programme.title: Twenty Years Of Feminist Filmmaking
programme.desc: A clip montage for presentation at the National Action Committee on the Status of Women to commemorate the 20th anniversary of Studio D and the National Action Committee.

programme.title: Waiting
programme.desc: The patient Dinkas of South Sudan endure famine amid civil strife. Aid arrives in Alek, but distribution is delayed to prevent unrest, revealing the stark reality of hunger.

programme.title: Children Of War
programme.desc: A remarkable documentary in which teenagers from war-torn countries, filmed in interaction with Canadian high-school students, speak with dignity, maturity and candor about the struggles of their people and the suffering they have endured.

programme.title: Safe Distance, A
programme.desc: A Safe Distance examines the services needed by and available to battered women. The film looks at some innovative approaches to providing services and accommodation for battered women in rural, northern, and Native communities.

programme.title: Le Grand Serpent Du Monde
programme.desc: A young forty-something, Tom Paradise refuses to grow up. Behind the wheel of his bus he drives endlessly through the city, tracing out the path of his life, dreaming of the landscape of the American West that forever impressed him

programme.title: Koromousso Big Sister
programme.desc: This film challenges cultural taboos surrounding female sexuality and explores the fight to take back ownership of bodies and to overcome the trauma of female genital mutilation.

programme.title: The Man Who Stole Dreams
programme.desc: This enchanting and magical animation film, an ode to our dreams during the night, celebrates the creative imagination, uniqueness, and the human spirit. The plot involves a man who steals the dreams of villagers, the tries to sell them back to the them.

programme.title: The Way It Is
programme.desc: The Way It Is" explores divorce's effects on a family, centered on twelve-year-old Helen. Her journey to acceptance offers insights for all ages, suitable for family-life courses, single-parent groups, and counseling.

programme.title: Turnaround A Story Of Recovery
programme.desc: Turnaround: A Story of Recovery" follows five women battling addiction at Aurora House. This documentary offers insight for families, friends, and professionals interested in alternative treatment methods.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in der Wachau und Bruck an der Mur
programme.desc: Viele Stars der Volksmusik begleiten Dagmar Obernosterer durch die malerische Hügellandschaft der Wachau. Petra Frey, Oswald Sattler, Simone u.v.a. verwöhnen Sie auf der Reise von Dürnstein über Bruck a. d. Mur bis nach Gamlitz mit ihren Liedern.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in der Wachau und Bruck an der Mur

programme.title: Tanzparty
programme.desc: Ein Bett im Kornfeld / One For You, One For Me / Love Is In The Air / Ma baker / Na Na Hey Hey Goodbye / How Do You Do / Dolce vita / Maria Magdalena / Das gewisse Gefühl

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten
programme.desc: Eine herrliche Bergkulisse und traumhafter Pistenspaß - die Grubertaler und Marc Pircher bringen eine ordentliche Portion Hüttenzauber in Ihr Wohnzimmer. Hochkarätige Interpreten wie Mara Kayser, Oswald Sattler & Doris Russo sind ebenfalls mit dabei..
programme.sub-title: Rund um die Petzen Winterlust in der Region Klopeinersee /Südkärnten

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Osttirol und Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer erkundet den Drauradweg von Osttirol nach Kärnten. Die Stars der Volksmusik singen dabei ihre Hits vor der einzigartigen Bergkulisse der Lienzer Dolomiten. Ob Kurt Elsasser, Alexandra Lexer u.v.a. den Drauradweg zum Schwingen bringen.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Osttirol und Kärnten

programme.title: Goldies: Folge 2
programme.desc: Er schenkte mir den Eiffelturm / Verlieben, verloren, vergessen, verzeihn / Theater / Moskau / Let your love flow / Rocky / Mississippi

programme.title: Schlagergala 2006: Teil 1
programme.desc: Das "Who Is Who" der deutschen Schlagerszene gibt sich ein Stelldichein und GoldStar TV ist live dabei! Stars wie Nino de Angelo, Mary Roos, Johnny Logan, Kristina Bach, Jürgen Drews und Karel Gott präsentieren ihre Hits im westfälischen Legenden.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Villnösser Tal in Südtirol
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert wieder die Stars der volkstümlichen Schlagermusik - diesmal vor der malerischen Kulisse des Villnösser Tals in Südtirol. Mit dabei sind unter anderem Oswald Sattler, die Zellberg Buam und Anneliese Breitenberger.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast im Villnösser Tal in Südtirol

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Defereggental / Antholzertal
programme.desc: Die Stars der Volksmusik begleiten Dagmar Obernosterer vom Defereggental in Osttirol in das Antholzertal nach Südtirol. Gottfried Würcher, die jungen Zillertaler, Sarah-Stephanie, die Alpenrebellen u.v.a. sind dabei, wenn die Apres-Ski-Party beginnt.

programme.title: Olaf Henning - Volles Programm: Teil 1
programme.desc: GoldStar TV präsentiert Ihnen Olaf Hennings Konzert "Volles Programm". Freuen Sie sich auf den beliebten Schlager-Star aus dem Ruhrgebiet und seine besten Hits zum Mitsingen. Ein Muß für jeden Henning-Fan!

programme.title: Freddy Quinn LIVE - Lieder, die das Leben schrieb: Teil 1
programme.desc: Er reiste um die Welt, begeisterte ein Millionenpublikum und schaffte es zehn Mal auf Platz 1 der deutschen Charts. Freddy Quinn ist einer der letzten großen Entertainer Deutschlands. 2002 gab der Österreicher ein bewegendes Abschieds-Konzert in Wien.

programme.title: Andreas Fulterer - Mein Weg
programme.desc: Andreas Fulterer ist seiner Heimat Südtirol immer treu geblieben. Im Musikspecial "Mein Weg" zeigt er uns die schönsten Plätze und ist zudem mit seinen größten Hits in Konzertausschnitten zu sehen. Ein wunderschöner, besinnlicher Musikfilm.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Brandnertal
programme.desc: In dieser Ausgabe von "Lieder, Land & Leute" entführt Sängerin und Moderatorin Dagmar Obernosterer die Zuschauer in das wunderschöne Brandnertal. Vor der alpinen Kulisse des Vorarlberg geben Stars aus Schlager und Volsmusik ihre Lieder zum Besten.

programme.title: Gala der Stars auf hoher See
programme.desc: GoldStar TV sendet von der 'Costa Classica'. Frederic Meisner und Jutta Niedhardt stellen Ihnen das Traumschiff vor. Für musikalische Unterhaltung ist selbstverständlich auch gesorgt. Freuen Sie sich auf Stars wie Roland Kaiser, WIND, André Stade u.v.a

programme.desc: Colette dirige uma cafetaria conhecida pelo seu chocolate quente secreto e famoso. Marcus, um novo dono de sobremesa, começa a atrair os clientes da Colette, ela está determinada a expô-lo.

programme.title: Sobrevivendo Às Festas com Parentes
programme.desc: As irmãs Miranda e Lyla se reúnem para o Natal com suas famílias. Ao longo de três dias, alegria e caos causam estragos nos planos de férias das famílias e as antigas rivalidades entre irmãos surgem para sabotar a esperança diversão de fim de ano.

programme.title: Um Natal Encantado
programme.desc: Hugo, de doze anos, ainda acredita em elfos, mas é provocado por seus colegas, então decide se forçar a crescer. Mas quando sua família sai de férias de Natal, ele descobre que elfos moram no hotel.

programme.title: O Desejo de Charlie
programme.desc: Um veterano militar volta para casa depois de um afastamento por estresse pós-traumático. Com seu novo cachorro, ele descobre em pleno Natal um novo propósito em sua vida - auxiliar ex-militares que precisam de ajuda.

programme.title: O milagre de natal Jonathan Toomey
programme.desc: Quando um menino perde o presépio de madeira que o liga ao pai morto, sua mãe preocupada convence um entalhador solitário e mal-humorado a criar um substituto e permitir que seu filho o veja trabalhar nele.

programme.title: Só Pode Ser Amor
programme.desc: Durante a temporada de Natal, três irmãs terão que decidir o que fazer com sua vida romântica quando partem para encontrar a família para as festas e seus respectivos pares surgem na cidade para tentar uma segunda chance.

programme.title: Aventuras do K-9: Uma História de Natal
programme.desc: Kassie, suas amigas e seu cachorro, Scoot, organizam um evento de arrecadação de fundos de férias, mas precisam proteger o dinheiro de alguns bandidos para salvar o Natal.

programme.title: Um Anjo em Minha Vida
programme.desc: Uma jovem adolescente rica e mimada está prestes a descobrir que o verdadeiro valor não está nas etiquetas de preços e "coisas", mas nos atos gentis de ajudar os outros, tudo com a mão amiga de um anjo da guarda.

programme.title: Desejo de Natal
programme.desc: Sem dinheiro e abandonada pelo marido com três filhos, Martha não está tendo o melhor fim de ano da sua vida. Mas ela muda de cidade e redescobre a esperança quando encontra um emprego e uma rede de apoio em uma pacata lanchonete de interior.

programme.title: Músicas de Natal
programme.desc: Crie uma atmosfera calorosa de férias em sua casa com as imagens e sons do Natal, filmados em alta definição.

programme.title: Lareira Festiva
programme.desc: Cozy up to the special edition fireplace, just in time for the Holidays. The soft crackling of burning wood will turn your home into a calming retreat.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Una Esperanza de Navidad
programme.desc: Esta es una encantadora y conmovedora historia navideña sobre la esperanza, el perdón y la fe, que cuenta cómo una madre soltera y su única hija de siete años encuentran un Santa Claus que puede cambiar sus vidas.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una navidad real
programme.desc: Una ejecutiva de publicidad muy trabajadora, se enamora de un consultor que es un príncipe disfrazado.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Una Esperanza de Navidad
programme.desc: Esta es una encantadora y conmovedora historia navideña sobre la esperanza, el perdón y la fe, que cuenta cómo una madre soltera y su única hija de siete años encuentran un Santa Claus que puede cambiar sus vidas.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una navidad real
programme.desc: Una ejecutiva de publicidad muy trabajadora, se enamora de un consultor que es un príncipe disfrazado.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.desc: Ronettes (Sleigh Ride) / Justin Bieber (Mistletoe) / Mel And Kim (Rockin' Around The Christmas Tree) / Shawn Mendes & Camila Cabello (The Christmas Song) / Mike Oldfield (In Dulci Jubilo) / Paul McCartney (Wonderful Christmas Time)
programme.sub-title: Ronettes / Justin Bieber / Mel And Kim / Shawn Mendes & Camila Cabello / Mike Oldfield / Paul McCartney

programme.title: MTV Xmas
programme.desc: Frankie Goes To Hollywood (The Power Of Love) / Zara Larsson (Invisible) / ABBA (Little Things) / Paul McCartney (Wonderful Christmas Time) / Ed Sheeran (Perfect)
programme.sub-title: Frankie Goes To Hollywood / Zara Larsson / ABBA / Paul McCartney / Ed Sheeran

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: El campamento de Santa
programme.desc: Cansados ​​de niños traviesos, ingratos y egocéntricos, los elfos de Santa se declaran en huelga. Para salvar la Navidad, Santa Claus trae a su campo de entrenamiento a seis jóvenes sin escrúpulos para enseñarles a hacer juguetes.

programme.title: Ballet para Navidad
programme.desc: Un video de Michel aprendiendo ballet con su hija lo convierte en el soltero más codiciado de la ciudad.

programme.title: Una Esperanza de Navidad
programme.desc: Esta es una encantadora y conmovedora historia navideña sobre la esperanza, el perdón y la fe, que cuenta cómo una madre soltera y su única hija de siete años encuentran un Santa Claus que puede cambiar sus vidas.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una navidad real
programme.desc: Una ejecutiva de publicidad muy trabajadora, se enamora de un consultor que es un príncipe disfrazado.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL

Hier gibt es viele Wälder, jeder mit seinem eigenen Ökosystem. Iberische Gebirgsketten haben unterschiedliche Gesichter und Persönlichkeiten, ebenso wie ihre wilden Bewohner.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Die Formen der Fortpflanzung in der Natur sind sehr unterschiedlich, und nicht immer gehört Sex dazu. Grundsätzlich werben die Männchen um die Weibchen, die den stärksten oder schönsten Kandidaten wählen, den mit den meisten Vorzügen oder, wenn sie Glück haben, den besten Vater.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Patagonien
programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Kanadas Küstenwölfe
programme.desc: Der Great Bear Regenwald an der Westküste Kanadas ist die Heimat der Küstenwölfe. Sie haben felsige Riffe, bewaldete Inseln und die tobende Pazifikküste zu ihrer Heimat gemacht. Das besondere an ihnen ist, dass sie nicht nur an Land jagen, sondern auch im Ozean. Die Dokumentation begleitet Naturführer Cal Humchitt und sein Team auf den Spuren der Küstenwölfe.

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Ägypten
programme.desc: Ägypten bedeutet Pharaonen, Pyramiden und vor allem – Wüste. In der feindlichen Umgebung leben alle Arten von Tieren. Die alten Ägypter glaubten, dass diese Kreaturen die Natur, Mond, Tag und Nacht kontrollieren.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Das Meer verwandelt sich zusehends. Die azurblaue See von Durban unterscheidet sich grundlegend von der rauen Meeresküste des Kaps. Gemeinsam mit dem österreichischen Haiforscher Dietmar Posch startet Andreas auf eine Expedition in die warmen Gewässer vor der Küste

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Berge sind für die gesamte Morphologie Iberiens verantwortlich. Sie sind auch der Geburtsort der Flüsse, die das Leben im gesamten Gebiet verteilen. Hier gibt es viele Wälder, jeder mit seinem eigenen Ökosystem. Iberische Gebirgsketten haben unterschiedliche Gesichter und Persönlichkeiten, ebenso wie ihre wilden Bewohner.

programme.desc: Extremangler Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf der Suche nach einem Killerfisch tief nach Mittelamerika.

programme.title: Der Atlantische Tarpun
programme.desc: Der Angler Jeremy Wade trotzt auf der Suche nach einem Monsterfisch der Strahlung in Tschernobyl.

programme.title: Der Neuseeland-Aal
programme.desc: Der Extremangler Jeremy Wade reist nach Papua-Neuguinea.

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana
programme.desc: Im Herzen der Maremma, der Küstenregion der Toskana, werden auf einer Azienda seit mehr als 1000 Jahren Rinder und Pferde gezüchtet. Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: Das ayurvedische Wissen wird seit Jahrhunderten in den Familien der Vaidijas bewahrt - und auch von der Schulmedizin akzeptiert und praktiziert. Krankheiten wie Arthritis oder Diabetes entstehen gemäß Ayurveda durch toxische Stoffe, wenn die drei biophysiologischen Kräfte des Körpers - die sogenannten Doshas - aus dem Gleichgewicht geraten.

programme.title: Kambodscha
programme.desc: Tiere, die in Europa Abscheu und Ekel verursachen, werden in Kambodscha gejagt, gegessen oder zum Verzehr verkauft. Jedes Jahr während der Regenzeit steigt das Wasser des Tonl? Sap Sees um viele Meter. Im September machen die Fischer daher immer weniger Fänge. Deshalb weichen sie auf Ratten aus: Die Tiere leben bei Hochwasser auf den Bäumen und ernähren sich von Früchten.

programme.title: Yoga
programme.desc: Es heißt, Yoga werde in Indien schon seit rund 5000 Jahren praktiziert. Doch unter der britischen Kolonialherrschaft geriet das Wissen um die medizinischen Heilkräfte von Yoga nahezu in Vergessenheit. In den 1930er Jahren entwickelte der Yoga-Meister B.K.S. Iyengar aus der altindischen Hatha-Tradition neue Techniken. Iyengar-Yoga wird inzwischen weltweit praktiziert und anerkannt.

programme.title: Vietnam
programme.desc: Im vietnamesischen Dorf Vinh Son lebt ein Großteil der Einwohner von der Schlangenzucht: Kobras, Gebänderte Rattenschlangen und sogar die extrem großen und giftigen Königskobras werden hier gehalten und verkauft - zumeist an den Nachbarn China. Der Vorsitzende des örtlichen Zuchtverbandes Kim Van Hoc war einer der ersten, der das lukrative Geschäft noch zu kommunistischen Zeiten entwickelte.

programme.title: Insekten
programme.desc: In der Natur gehören Insekten seit jeher auf den Speiseplan. Nur der Mensch macht vielerorts lange einen Bogen um sie. Heute ernähren sich bereits zwei Milliarden Menschen von den kleinen Krabbeltieren, vornehmlich in Afrika und Asien. Und langsam kommt auch Europa auf den Geschmack.

programme.title: Burundi
programme.desc: Désiré Nininahazwe, Familienvater und Gründer eines Start ups, kam zum ersten Mal mit dem Trommeln in Kontakt, als er ins SOS-Kinderdorf nach Bujumbura kam, nachdem er seine Eltern im Bürgerkrieg verloren hatte.

programme.title: Madagaskar
programme.sub-title: Die junge Generation im Spannungsfeld des Klimawandels
programme.desc: Während man im westlichen Ausland an Vanilleplantagen und Tropenwälder denkt, spricht man in Madagaskar nur noch von Kéré, der schlimmsten Dürre seit 40 Jahren. Hoffnung gibt, dass sich die SOS-Kinderdörfer um die Kinder des Dorfes kümmern.

programme.title: Sri Lanka
programme.desc: Der fast 30 Jahre währende Bürgerkrieg im Süden Sri Lankas hat das Land verändert. Hunderte Kinder und Waisen standen auf der Straße. Dank der SOS-Kinderdörfer weltweit konnten die meisten in den sechs Kinderdörfern versorgt werden.

programme.title: Nach dem Wasser
programme.desc: Ein Erdbeben vor Sumatra löste 2004 den Tsunami aus. Der Film schildert die Umstände in der Region Aceh und wie die SOS-Kinderdörfer es schafften, Nothilfe zu leisten und bis heute mit ihren Programmen Kindern und Erwachsenen zu helfen.

programme.title: Big Bugs
programme.desc: Von der Massenwanderung der Monarchfalter zu den Turnieren der Hirschkäfer – dieser Film zeigt die spektakulärsten Wesen auf mehr als vier Beinen und ihre kuriosen Lebensgewohnheiten. Sie gehören zu den erfolgreichsten Tieren auf unserem Planeten - 80 Prozent aller bekannten Arten sind Gliederfüßer. Unter ihnen sind die größten Sonderlinge der Natur: Spinnen, die unter Falltüren lauern, Schmetterlinge, die Kontinente überqueren, Käfer, die einander vom Baum werfen oder gewiefte Konstrukteure von Treibsand-Fallen. Extreme Zeitlupenaufnahmen und innovative Makro-Kameratechniken erlauben neue Einblicke in das Leben der kleinen Wundertiere.

programme.title: Flügel, Schnabel, Superhirn
programme.desc: Jahrzehnte lang glaubten wir Menschen, Vögel wären schlichte Gemüter und hauptsächlich von ihren Instinkten geleitet. Erst vor relativ kurzer Zeit mussten wir entdecken, wie falsch diese Annahme war. Während der Dreharbeiten für diesen Film, der von Terra Mater Factual Studios und Parthenon Entertainment hergestellt wurde, besuchten die Regisseure John Capener und Steve Nicholls Forscherautoritäten des Konrad Lorenz- und des Max Planck-Instituts und der Universitäten Wien, Oxford, Cambridge und Straßburg und stießen auf erstaunliche Intelligenzleistungen.

programme.title: Popa Chubby
programme.sub-title: Popa Chubby - It's A Mighty Hard Road
programme.desc: Popa Chubby, born as Ted Horowitz, is an American blues singer and guitarist, who has become one of the most popular figures of New York's blues scene. Early on in his career he released the album 'Booty and the Beast' (1995), which became one of the 1990s's best-selling blues albums. Chubby describes his own style as "The Stooges meets Buddy Guy, Motörhead meets Muddy Waters, and Jimi Hendrix meets Robert Johnson". As part of the French music festival Blues sur Seine, Chubby and his band played a great blues rock concert, showcasing the artist's powerful and soulful guitar playing. This performance was recorded at Théâtre Simone Signoret on November 8, 2019.

programme.title: Philip Catherine, Jean-Louis Rassinfosse & Chet Baker
programme.sub-title: Jazz a la Grand Place Chet Baker Trio
programme.desc: Two top-tier Belgian musicians – guitarist Philip Catherine and bassist Jean-Louis Rassinfosse – accompany American jazz trumpeter and vocalist Chet Baker during this 1985 performance at the beautiful Brussels Jazz Club, located on the Grand-Place, the Belgian capital's central square. The trio plays Charlie Mariano's “Crystal Bells”, the title track of their acclaimed 1983 album. Other songs played during this legendary concert include “Down” and “How Deep is the Ocean”.

programme.title: John Coltrane
programme.sub-title: I want to talk about you
programme.desc: Explore the music of one of the most influential and innovative saxophonists in jazz history: John Coltrane! Immerse yourself in this collection of remarkable performances from the early 1960s that showcase Coltrane's unparalleled artistry and unique sound during a transformative period in the artist's career. Recorded in various European cities, Coltrane is seen playing the songs “Autumn Leaves”, “Hackensack”, “My Favorite Things”, “I Want To Talk About You”, “Vigil”, and “Naima”. Tune in and experience why the music of John Coltrane has touched the lives of so many!

programme.title: B.B.King
programme.sub-title: B.B. King Orchestra - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Back in 1979, legendary American blues guitarist B.B. King gave an unforgettable performance for the audience in The Hague. Born in 1925 in a small town in Mississippi, 'Lucille' (as he nicknamed his guitar) helped him escape a miserable existence picking cotton. He arrived in Memphis in the late 1940s, where his cousin Bukka White taught him the tricks of the blues. Soon he developed his own style. King's virtuoso, narrative solos with lots of vibrato, have been an inspiration for most (rock) guitarists after him.

programme.title: Buddy Rich, Tom Warrington, Bob Kaye & John Marshall
programme.sub-title: Buddy Rich Big Band - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Buddy Rich, one of the most influential jazz drummers of all time, performed at the North Sea Jazz Festival of 1978 with his orchestra. Rich's drumming was known for its remarkable speed and dexterity, which he achieved without any formal education.

programme.title: Eurythmics
programme.desc: Annie Lennox and Dave Stewart came from very different backgrounds, but both pursued a career in music from an early age. Annie Lennox and Dave Stewart were two wildly different characters. She was a tenement girl from Aberdeen, who'd managed to claw her way out of what was obviously quite a hard upbringing, He was the kind of Wearside Durham Jack the Lad who was something of a musical prodigy. Annie studied the flute at the Royal Academy of Music but had to work as a waitress to get by. It was at her workplace that she was introduced to Dave Stewart through a mutual friend. They would soon form their first band, The Tourists The Tourists disbanded after legal issues between Pete Coombes and the label. It freed Annie and Dave, who wanted to expand their creativity further. Together they formed the Eurythmics and released their debut album, In the Garden. In the Garden achieved little commercial success and the duo chose to retreat to a small home studio in London's Chalk Farm, where they were free to develop a new sound They began to work with synthesisers, a choice that would lead them to their breakthrough hit, Sweet Dreams Are Made Of This. The success of the single led to a re-release of Love is a Stranger. The band, now big on both sides of the Atlantic, had another hit on their hands. The band quickly worked on their follow-up album, Touch. It would become their first number one in the UK and produced a succession of hit singles. Touch also saw them experiment with even more musical styles Featuring archive material, music videos Who's That Girl, Sweet Dreams (Are Made Of This) and, exclusive insights from music critics and journalists Michael Bonner (Uncut Magazine), Hamish MacBain (Shortlist), John Aizlewood (Evening Standard) Rock Legends Eurythmics tells the story of one of Britain's enduring rock bands.

programme.title: Bryan Ferry
programme.desc: Bryan Ferry was born into a northern working-class family as the Second World War came to a close. His father handled pit ponies for the surrounding coal mines. Whilst studying fine art at Newcastle University, Ferry became exposed to the R&B, jazz and soul records that came in via the city's shipping ports. Ferry moved to London's Notting Hill at the start of the 1970s. It was here that he would quickly form his band, Roxy Music. He had such a strong vision for the band that before signing to Island Records he had the band's debut album and artwork completed. The first single, Virginia Plain was so remarkable in its maturity it entered the UK charts at number four .

programme.title: Philippe Herreweghe, Collegium Vocale Gent, Dorothee Mields & Thomas Hobbs
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe conducts his Collegium Vocale Gent in this chamber music program dedicated to the music of J. S. Bach. On the program are Bach's Orchestral Suite No. 4 in D major, BWV 1069 Gott der Herr ist Sonn und Schild, BWV 79 and Missa brevis in G major, BWV 236. The soloists are soprano Dorothee Mields, tenor Thomas Hobbs, countertenor Alex Potter, and bass Peter Kooij. The program continues with a fine selection of Bach's works performed by French lutenist Thomas Dunford. On the program are Suite for lute in G minor, BWV 995 Suite for solo cello in G major (arr. for lute), BWV 1007 and Chaconne from Partita for solo violin in D minor (arr. lute), BWV 1004. This concert was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, in 2017.

programme.title: Raphael Pichon, Ensemble Pygmalion, Sabine Devieilhe & Arnaud de Pasquale
programme.sub-title: Mozart - A Gala for the Weber Sisters
programme.desc: On March 23, 1783, Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart gave a successful concert at Vienna's Burgtheater that he dedicated to two sopranos: Aloysia and Josepha Weber, the sisters of his wife Constanze. The concert's program would be considered odd by today's standards. The composer's Symphony No. 35 was broken up and interspersed with other compositions, such as concertos, arias, and works for solo piano. Nearly two and a half centuries later, French soprano Sabine Devieilhe, conductor Raphaël Pichon and his Ensemble Pygmalion bring a wonderful concert inspired by that remarkable event. The program includes: ‘Allegro con spirito' of Symphony No. 35, also known as the Haffner Symphony ‘Vorrei spiegarvi, oh Dio', KV 418 ‘Schon lacht der holde Frühling', KV 580 Trio of ‘Die Schlittenfahrt' No. 3, KV 605 Deutscher Tanz No. 6, KV 571 ‘Der Hölle Rache kocht in meinem Herzen' from Mozart's opera Die Zauberflöte ‘Finale: Presto' of Symphony No. 35 ‘Nehmt meinen Dank', KV 383 and ‘Dans un bois solitaire et sombre', KV 308. This performance was recorded at Théâtre Impérial de Compiègne, in Compiègne, France.

programme.title: Jodie Devos, Anaik Morel & David Violi
programme.sub-title: Tribute to French Romanticism at Venice
programme.desc: Salon Romantique à Venise salutes the work of the Palazzetto Bru Zane foundation which aims to contribute to the rediscovery of a neglected part of the French musical heritage running from Louis XVi to WW I. This concert offers a journey into the French romantic repertoire performed by pianist David Violi (piano), Jodie Devos (soprano) and Anaik Morel (mezzo-soprano). The program contains some of the most beloved French arias, such as 'Seguedille' from Bizet's Carmen by Bizet, the Flower Duet from Delibes' Lakmé and 'Mon cœur s'ouvre à ta voix' from Saint-Saëns Samson et Dalila. Recorded at the Palazzetoo Bru Zane in Venice, Italy in 2016.

programme.title: Rodolfo Mederos, Otros Aires, Teresa Parodi & Café de los Maestros
programme.desc: For the audience in the famous ballroom El Palacio in Buenos Aires, the year 2012 began with tango rhythms and Argentinean folk music. This festive broadcast opens with a tango performance by dance partners Eduardo and Gloria, accompanied by the renowned ensemble Café de los Maestros. Another highlights is a performance by bandoneon player Rodolfo Mederos and his trio. In addition, the concert features a performance by Teresa Parodi, former lead singer of the Astor Piazzolla Band, accompanied by the Fernando Suárez Paz Quintet. Also on the bill is the contemporary electronic tango formation Otros Aires. Founded by Miguel Di Genova in 2003, Otros Aires combines electronic rhythms and traditional tango instruments, such as the bandoneon, piano, and guitar. On the program are compositions by Astor Piazzolla, Pedro Maffia, Pedro Laurenz, Gustavo Mozzi, and many others. Enjoy this concert of music and dance, featuring some of Argentine's tango scene's finest artists!

programme.title: Federico Guglielmo & Roberto Loreggian
programme.sub-title: Works by Matteis, Tartini, Bach & Vivaldi
programme.desc: The six-concert series “Io suono italiano” is dedicated to music of Italian composers and performed by Italian musicians on Italian instruments. The concert programs cover four centuries of music: from Girolamo Frescobaldi and Antonio Vivaldi to more contemporary music by Ennio Morricone and Azio Corghi. Each program presents more familiar pieces alongside lesser-known compositions. These performances were filmed at the atmospheric Teatro Sociale in Rovigo, Italy, in January 2021. In this program, Federico Guglielmo (violin) and Roberto Loreggian (harpsichord) present Baroque music. On the program are Nicola Matteis's Passaggio rotto e Andamento veloce per violino solo (from Ayres for the Violini), Giuseppe Tartini's Sonata in G minor Op. 1 No. 10 (B.g10) “Didone abbandonata”, J. S. Bach's Concerto in F major for solo harpsichord, BWV 978 (a transcription of Antonio Vivaldi's Violin Concerto in G major, Op. 3 No. 3, RV 310), and Vivaldi's Sonata IV in D major, RV 755.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - String Quartet No. 7 & 13, and Op. 133
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 7 in F major, Op. 59, No. 1, known as “Razumovsky” String Quartet No. 13 in B-flat major, Op. 130 and the monumental Great Fugue, Op. 133. This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 12, 2020.

programme.desc: Von der Massenwanderung der Monarchfalter zu den Turnieren der Hirschkäfer – dieser Film zeigt die spektakulärsten Wesen auf mehr als vier Beinen und ihre kuriosen Lebensgewohnheiten. Sie gehören zu den erfolgreichsten Tieren auf unserem Planeten - 80 Prozent aller bekannten Arten sind Gliederfüßer. Unter ihnen sind die größten Sonderlinge der Natur: Spinnen, die unter Falltüren lauern, Schmetterlinge, die Kontinente überqueren, Käfer, die einander vom Baum werfen oder gewiefte Konstrukteure von Treibsand-Fallen. Extreme Zeitlupenaufnahmen und innovative Makro-Kameratechniken erlauben neue Einblicke in das Leben der kleinen Wundertiere.

Während der Dreharbeiten für diesen Film, der von Terra Mater Factual Studios und Parthenon Entertainment hergestellt wurde, besuchten die Regisseure John Capener und Steve Nicholls Forscherautoritäten des Konrad Lorenz- und des Max Planck-Instituts und der Universitäten Wien, Oxford, Cambridge und Straßburg und stießen auf erstaunliche Intelligenzleistungen.

programme.title: Die Verwandlungskünstler von Dakar
programme.desc: Dakar, die Hauptstadt Senegals: Hier zu überleben, ist für viele Menschen eine Frage der Improvisation. In vielen Vierteln hat die Not einen ganz eigenen Boom hervorgebracht: Die Menschen sammeln, was andere weggeworfen haben - und wandeln diese Abfälle in Neues? um. Wir zeigen, wie alte Konservendosen in Spielzeugautos, Lampen und Koffer verwandelt werden, Kronkorken in Körbe, Motoren in Kochtöpfe, Autoreifen in Eimer. So entstehen Gebrauchsgegenstände, aber auch Spielzeuge und Möbelstücke, die in Europa bereits als Kleinkunst gehandelt werden. Der 31-Jährige Malick Mbaye weiß zu schätzen, was andere Menschen wegwerfen: Büchsen, Dosen und Flaschendeckel - oder alte Paletten. Zusammen mit seinem Kompagnon Alassane Diop, 26, bastelt er daraus mit meist improvisierten Werkzeugen Kommoden, Koffer oder Gießkannen, aber auch Spielzeug. Sogar aus Europa erhalten die beiden inzwischen Aufträge. Mit ihrer kleinen Werkstatt Soweto Village? können sie ihre Eltern und Geschwister ernähren, für eigene Familien allerdings reicht das bescheidene Einkommen nicht. Lebenstraum der beiden ist es, eines Tages alle Freunde und Verwandte beschäftigen zu können.Schon jetzt ist ihre Veranda sozialer Mittelpunkt der Nachbarschaft. Ganze Stadtteile Dakars leben von der Müll-Verwandlung. Aus Mangel an ...

programme.title: Die Marmorberge von Italien
programme.desc: Die Apuanischen Alpen im Nordwesten der Toskana beherbergen eines der größten Marmorvorkommen der Welt. Seit der Römerzeit wird hier der weltberühmte Carrara-Marmor abgebaut. Mit allen Mitteln der Technik ringt der Mensch dem Berg das wertvolle Gestein ab und transportiert es auf halsbrecherischen Wegen ins Tal, von wo aus seine Reise in die ganze Welt beginnt. Am frühen Morgen fährt der Bildhauer Renzo Maggi zum 1.300 Meter hoch gelegenen Marmorbruch von Monte Cervaiole. Bereits Michelangelo hat sich hier im 16. Jahrhundert seine gigantischen Marmorblöcke ausgesucht. Trotz moderner Technik wird die Marmorgewinnung größtenteils noch auf traditionelle Weise betrieben. Teilweise unter lebensgefährlichen Bedingungen: Extreme Wetterschwankungen und Nebel erschweren den Einsatz von schwerem Gerät. Auf halsbrecherischen Serpentinen wird die tonnenschwere Last dann hinab zum Hafen von Carrara gebracht, von wo aus der Marmor seine Reise in die ganze Welt antritt.

programme.title: Die letzten Cowboys der Toskana

Butteri, wie hier die Rinderhirten genannt werden, sind wind- und wetterfeste Kerle. Am ersten Mai steht die Merca? an, das ist der wichtigste Tag des Jahres für jeden Buttero. Dann werden die wildlebenden Kälber von den Müttern getrennt und wie anno dazumal mit Brandeisen markiert.

programme.title: Indien

Iyengar aus der altindischen Hatha-Tradition neue Techniken. Iyengar-Yoga wird inzwischen weltweit praktiziert und anerkannt.

programme.sub-title: La Entrevista Que Sacudio Al Mundo
programme.desc: En 1995, la Princesa Diana rompió protocolos en una impactante entrevista con BBC Panorama. 25 años después, este documental analiza cómo se orquestó la exclusiva del siglo, su impacto en la sociedad moderna y ofrece nuevas perspectivas sobre el retrato psicológico de Diana, quien creyó en un cuento de hadas y se perdió en las realidades de su matrimonio. Descubre la verdad detrás de este evento icónico.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: El Rey y su hermana, la Princesa Cristina, comparten sus recuerdos de infancia en el palacio. "En realidad no era un entorno agradable para vivir, más bien parecía un hotel", recuerda el Rey al describir las habitaciones donde él y sus hermanas crecieron en el ala sur del palacio. La Princesa Heredera Victoria nos muestra objetos de valor incalculable en sus habitaciones favoritas "Es un patrimonio cultural fantástico y es impresionante que se conserven estos ambientes, teniendo en cuenta lo antiguos que son. Es un tesoro extraordinario y accesible que nos pertenece a todos", afirma. Los espectadores también tienen la oportunidad de adentrarse entre bastidores antes de una visita de Estado, escuchar historias de fantasmas reales, así como a historiadores, expertos y artesanos que nos ofrecen un retrato único de un tesoro nacional: nuestro Palacio Real.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: Nos subimos a un andamio para averiguar más cosas sobre la renovación de la fachada y llegar al fondo de la cuestión de si el viejo castillo está embrujado. Síganos por los salones dorados y las oscuras bóvedas de los sótanos. El Palacio Real de Estocolmo tiene más de mil habitaciones y cientos de años de historia real. El Rey y su hermana, la princesa Cristina, nos cuentan cómo fue crecer en el palacio. La Princesa Victoria muestra objetos de valor incalculable.

programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널우포늪엔 얼마만큼의 시간이 흘렀을까, 강물이 내어준 곳에 자연이 들어차고 그 주인으로 온갖 생명들이 살고 있습니다. 보이지 않지만 무수한 분초가 흐르듯 우포늪의 계절이 흐르는 소리는 신비롭죠. 들리나요? 보일듯 보이지 않는 무수한 반짝거림. 일렁임. 찰랑거림. 그 모든 시간의 자연이 조화롭게 돌아가는 소리. ※ 경상남도 창녕군 우포늪 (천연기념물 제524호)

programme.title: 풍요로운 다과 한상. 궁중병과 가을상
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널성큼 다가온 가을과 딱 맞는 궁중병과 가을차림상, 풍요로운 과실을 가득 담은 꽃송편, 가을하면 빠질 수 없는 밤과 대추를 맛있게 졸인 숙실과(생란, 율란, 조란), 그리고 환절기 감기를 물리쳐줄 달달하고 따뜻한 배숙을 준비했습니다. 우리모두 눈으로 먹으러가요! (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: 봄을 맞이하다. 궁중병과 봄차림상
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널봄과 가장 잘 어울리는 완벽한 간식, 궁중병과를 만드는 소리를 담아봤습니다. 봄향기 가득한 화사한 진달래로 만드는 진달래 화전, 다양한 재료로 예쁘게 색을 낸 삼색쌀강정, 그리고 달콤하고 톡 쏘는 오미자 화채를 만드는 모습을 함께 감상해보시죠. (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: 어둠 속 빛을 새기다. 나전장
programme.desc: 나전장은 칠기의 바탕 위에 나전 문양을 장식하여 나전 칠기를 제작하는 기능 또는 그 장인을 말합니다. 대개 나무 바탕에 삼베나 모시를 바르고 칠을 한 다음 자개를 붙이고 연마하기 때문에 통상 나전에는 '칠기'라는 말이 붙지요. 이형만 나전장의 화려한 '석류문 과반'이 만들어지는 과정을 살펴봐요. (이형만 / 국가무형문화재 나전장 보유자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: [궁궐 속 비밀의 화원] 창덕궁 낙선재 후원 EP.5
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [마음이 차분해지는 정원] 담양 소쇄원
programme.desc: 담양 소쇄원은 양산보(梁山甫: 1503~1557)가 스승인 조광조가 유배되자 세상의 뜻을 버리고 고향으로 내려와 깨끗하고 시원하다는 의미를 담아 조성한 정원입니다. 이 아름다운 정원은 조선시대를 대표하는 정원으로, 우리나라 선비의 고고한 품성과 절의를 엿볼 수 있습니다. ※ 담양 소쇄원 (사적 제 304호, 명승 제 40호)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: [조선왕릉 가을 숲길] 세조의 회한이 담긴 숲, 광릉
programme.desc: 남양주의 광릉은 조선 제7대 왕 세조와 정희왕후가 잠들어있는 곳입니다. 이 광릉이 있는 광릉숲은 서울 여의도 면적의 30배 규모의 울창한 숲으로, 생태적 안정성과 종 다양성을 엿볼 수 있습니다. 산과 도로, 하천을 끼고 만들어진 광릉숲길을 함께 걸어봐요. ※ 남양주 광릉 (사적 제197호) / 조선왕릉 (2009년 유네스코 세계문화유산)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: [조선왕릉 가을 숲길] 숲길로 이어진 어머니와 아들, 태릉과 강릉
programme.desc: 서울의 태릉은 조선 제11대 왕 중종의 제2계비인 문정왕후가, 강릉은 조선 제13대 왕 명종과 명종비 인순왕후가 잠들어있는 곳입니다. 두 능은 연결되어있어 태릉에서 호젓한 숲길을 따라 30분 정도 걸으면 강릉까지 한번에 만날 수 있답니다. ※ 서울 태릉과 강릉 (사적 제201호) / 조선왕릉 (2009년 유네스코 세계문화유산)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널
